content.description: The Jetty is a long, narrow formation plus a few freestanding boulders located above Watson Lake's north boat ramp. The south and east sections face the boat ramp area. The vertical to overhanging south and north walls sport a variety of tall face and crack problems, the east end has a few good roof problems, and the west end features a number of freestanding boulders. Short approach and generally good rock quality. You might want pads and spotters for some of the taller problems.
